1
00:00:00,180 --> 00:00:05,400
A reason often given for belief in evolution 
is the apparent similarity between apes,  

2
00:00:05,400 --> 00:00:10,380
especially chimpanzees, and humans. What 
do the latest scientific discoveries in  

3
00:00:10,380 --> 00:00:14,700
genetics tell us about this supposed 
similarity? Do these findings support  

4
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:19,800
the theory of evolution, or what the Bible 
teaches? Today on Creation Magazine LIVE!

5
00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:39,660
Welcome to Creation Magazine 
LIVE, I'm Alexander Osborne

6
00:00:39,660 --> 00:00:44,400
and I'm Thomas Bailey. In the 1970s 
work began to compare the similarity  

7
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:48,120
between chimps and humans in an 
effort to support human evolution.

8
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:54,060
But it isn't enough to compare the morphology, 
that is, the form and appearance, legs, arms,  

9
00:00:54,060 --> 00:00:59,520
face, and so on, a comparison really needs to 
be made at the level of the genes and the DNA.

10
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:06,780
Based on early work comparing DNA a proponent of 
evolution, Richard Dawkins, claimed that chimps  

11
00:01:06,780 --> 00:01:12,180
and humans are nearly identical at the genetic 
level. In his book, "The Blind Watchmaker",  

12
00:01:12,180 --> 00:01:18,720
published in 1986, Dawkins claimed that humans 
share 99 percent of our genes with chimps.

13
00:01:19,543 --> 00:01:24,300
Dawkins claim of near identical genetic overlap 
between chimps and humans was later called,  

14
00:01:24,300 --> 00:01:27,000
'the myth of the one percent', by John Cohen,  

15
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:33,480
an evolutionary biologist in an article that 
appeared in the journal "Science" in 2007.

16
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:38,760
Why was it a myth? There are quite a few 
reasons. Firstly we'll need to realize  

17
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:43,800
that his claim wasn't based on a letter by 
letter comparison of the two sets of genetic  

18
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:49,200
information. The technology to do that kind 
of comparison didn't exist until the 1990s.

19
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:52,440
And even today it's challenging 
to compare two long sequences  

20
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:57,480
of DNA. Nevertheless a claimed 
overlap of 98.5 percent became  

21
00:01:57,480 --> 00:02:01,740
the 'gold standard' among evolutionary 
researchers and in the popular media.

22
00:02:01,740 --> 00:02:04,800
But we now know that the original work comparing  

23
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:08,940
chimp and human DNA had serious 
flaws. Let's consider a few.

24
00:02:08,940 --> 00:02:13,500
Number one: the first comparisons 
between chimp and human genes used  

25
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:18,600
only small snippets of DNA where it was 
assumed that overlap would be found.

26
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:22,860
Let's use an analogy to understand 
the issue. Pretend that you have  

27
00:02:22,860 --> 00:02:26,880
two different thousand piece puzzles and 
you want to know how similar they are.

28
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:31,380
If you match the blue pieces together 
you will find almost exact matches in  

29
00:02:31,380 --> 00:02:35,340
shape and color between some of 
the pieces from the two puzzles.

30
00:02:35,340 --> 00:02:40,080
But that isn't right. You have only 
compared a small portion of the pieces.  

31
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:43,200
So that's not a good indicator 
of how similar the puzzles are.

32
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:50,040
And that is the problem. One study compared 97 
protein coding sections of chimp DNA. But they're  

33
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:56,580
more than 234 000 protein coding sections 
in human DNA. So that's the first issue.

34
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:59,400
Number two, is that researchers didn't consider  

35
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:03,180
major portions of the DNA 
which they call junk DNA.

36
00:03:03,180 --> 00:03:09,000
So-called 'junk DNA' is part of the DNA 
supposedly left over from long ages of  

37
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:13,980
evolutionary processes. But we now know 
that there is no such thing as junk DNA.

38
00:03:13,980 --> 00:03:20,280
So true. Recent studies have shown that the 
areas of DNA between genes guide numerous,  

39
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:23,220
complex regulatory functions. For example,  

40
00:03:23,220 --> 00:03:27,900
controlling the extraction of information 
from genes for the creation of proteins.

41
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:30,720
Number three: it was discovered that the original  

42
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:35,100
samples of chimp DNA were 
contaminated with human DNA.

43
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:38,880
Wow! So there's evolutionary bias affecting  

44
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:42,060
how the experiments are set up, 
and now there's shoddy science.

45
00:03:42,060 --> 00:03:47,220
Right. Even a breath of a lab 
assistant can carry DNA and mix  

46
00:03:47,220 --> 00:03:51,960
with the sample being analyzed. This is 
like someone mixing blue pieces from two  

47
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:56,400
separate puzzles and comparing them to a 
picture of one of the original puzzles.

48
00:03:56,400 --> 00:04:01,200
Today proper DNA decoding requires 
that rigorous clean room procedures  

49
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:06,240
be followed. But the problem is even 
worse. The fourth flaw in the research is:  

50
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:12,480
an entire set of genetic information for 
chimps didn't yet exist. So it was assumed  

51
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:17,820
that the chimp DNA samples could be mapped 
to portions of the human genetic information.

52
00:04:18,420 --> 00:04:23,340
Think of the puzzles again. Let's say that 
one puzzle, once complete, will show children  

53
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:28,920
playing ball in the park under a blue sky with 
puffy clouds. But you don't have the original  

54
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:33,960
box with the picture, so you don't know yet what 
the completed picture is supposed to look like.

55
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:38,520
But since there are lots of blue pieces 
is you assume that they're for sky. So  

56
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:42,000
you take out a different puzzle box 
that has a picture of a blue sky with  

57
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:45,840
puffy clouds but they're are over a 
snow-capped mountain with forests.

58
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:50,220
Hold on! We know that using the 
picture of the second puzzle as  

59
00:04:50,220 --> 00:04:52,980
a guide is not going to help 
us assemble the first puzzle.

60
00:04:52,980 --> 00:04:57,600
Yup, but that's what the original 
researchers did. They assumed that  

61
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:01,740
chimp DNA would be like the human 
DNA when they made their comparisons.

62
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:07,860
So the original study that claimed a 98.5 
percent overlap between chimps and humans  

63
00:05:07,860 --> 00:05:14,460
used a biased assumption the researchers assumed 
that chimps and humans share a common set of DNA.  

64
00:05:14,460 --> 00:05:19,740
And that assumption was based on the belief that 
chimps and humans evolved from a common ancestor.

65
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:23,340
That was quite a while ago. Let's 
look at how things stand today.

66
00:05:23,340 --> 00:05:29,100
A complete map of common human DNA 
only became available recently. The  

67
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:33,180
Human Genome Project was launched in 1998, but the  

68
00:05:33,180 --> 00:05:38,580
goal of providing data on the complete 
genome wasn't achieved until May 2021.

69
00:05:38,580 --> 00:05:39,720
That's a long time.

70
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:43,920
That is a long time. It took over 20 
years of massive investment, effort,  

71
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:49,860
and the participation of many countries and 
labs to identify the core human DNA. And even  

72
00:05:49,860 --> 00:05:54,840
now the human genome information database 
is being refined, corrected and updated.

73
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:59,520
A fully complete map of chimp DNA 
doesn't exist yet. But a working  

74
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:05,460
version became available only in 2018. 
And as we'll see recent scientific work  

75
00:06:05,460 --> 00:06:10,320
indicates that humans are a completely 
different kind of creature from any ape.

76
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:15,000
There's no support in the DNA for the claim 
that chimps and humans evolved from a common  

77
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:23,400
ancestor. Rather, an analysis of DNA supports 
what the Bible states. In Genesis 1:24-25 God  

78
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:28,800
tells us that he created land animals, which 
included apes, by their kinds and then God  

79
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:35,160
created human beings as an entirely separate 
creation, as we read in Genesis 1:26-27.

80
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:40,320
Paul confirms this difference when he 
states, "For not all flesh is the same,  

81
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:46,200
but there is one kind for humans, another for 
animals, another for birds, and another for fish."

82
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:49,860
After the break we'll let you know 
how researchers arrived at today's  

83
00:06:49,860 --> 00:06:52,440
percentage match between chimps and humans.

84
00:06:54,360 --> 00:07:01,320
Helium gas is renowned for its ability to diffuse 
through materials quickly. Why is it then, that  

85
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:06,420
we find an abundance of helium in certain rock 
crystals that it has not managed to escape from  

86
00:07:06,420 --> 00:07:11,640
them? This has significant implications for the 
dating of rocks using radioactive decay. That's  

87
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:17,520
because helium is formed when some radioisotopes 
decay. And, therefore, lots of helium suggests  

88
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:22,860
lots of decay has occurred. Moreover, if lots 
of decay has occurred it also suggests that the  

89
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:28,560
rock is very old. However, nuclear physicist Dr 
Russell Humphreys realized that lots of helium  

90
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:32,760
trapped in the rock crystals that had not had 
time to diffuse out means that the rocks were  

91
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:37,620
actually young. Dr Humphreys concluded that 
nuclear decay rates must have been dramatically  

92
00:07:37,620 --> 00:07:42,420
faster in the recent past. And that is why rocks 
that are actually only thousands of years old  

93
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:48,180
are commonly wrongly dated using radioisotope 
decay as millions or billions of years old.  

